<Review ID>1744987
<Product Name>Rio One 64 MB MP3 Player
<Title>Just So-So
<Date>Sun Jul 27 00:00:00 CST 2003
<Content>I've owned a 32 mb Rio One for about 2 years now.  I've never had any of the hardware issues described by other reviewers, though I admit I treat it gently--it is an electronic device after all.  <p>I think it works well with music, but its lack of features make using it for audiobooks difficult.  There is no way to control the order of the tracks, except to FF or RW through them, so audiobook tracks play rather randomly.  As you can imagine, that is a real pain.  The lack of track display information only exacerbates this.  Overall, I'd say there are better MP3 players out there.  
<Overall>3

